            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en" resp="#VM">
                <p>This would be the first occurrence of the name, which then appears in <ref target="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0007.tlg002.perseus-grc1:4.3">Plu. Rom. 4.5</ref>, Ἄκκαν Λαρεντίαν in Rome. 
                    However, another version of the name (Ἄκα) is found on a millstone from Adrano (unpublished?) and on a locally produced hydria 
                    (the text is painted before firing) from Montagna di Marzo dating to the early 5th century BCE (Arena IGASM no. 121; 
                    <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020580">ISic020580</ref>). Another loom weight with identical inscription 
                    (<ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020574">ISic020574</ref>) was found in the same context.</p>
            </div>
